<h2>Alaka's Altanta Attemp</h2>		

<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_01" alt="entrance sign"/></div>
<p><em>The sign outside of the Gwinnett Center where the VGC occurred</em></p>

<p>What do a giant pink blob and a ghastly bug exoskeleton have in common? Both are terribly annoying end game win conditions based on the few things that can beat them being removed from play. The difference? The exoskeleton is much more commonly, and easily, teched against, and thus:</p>

<h3>The Team</h3>

<div><img src="/download/sprites/dp/465.png" alt="Abamasnow"/></div>
<p>
Abamasnow@Focus Sash<br/>
Quiet<br/>
252 HP, 252 SpAtk, 4 SpDef<br/>
~Blizzard<br/>
~Grass Knot<br/>
~Ice Shard<br/>
~Protect
</p>

<div><img src="/download/sprites/dp/382.png" alt="Kyogre"/></div>
<p>
Kyogre@Sitrus Berry<br/>
Modest<br/>
244 HP, 252 SpAtk, 12 Spe<br/>
~Blizzard<br/>
~Surf<br/>
~Thunder<br/>
~Protect
</p>

<div><img src="/download/sprites/dp/492.png" alt="Giratina"/></div>
<p>
Giratina@Yache Berry<br/>
Adamant<br/>
244 HP, 252 Atk, 12 Spe<br/>
~Shadow Force<br/>
~Shadow Sneak<br/>
~Dragon Claw<br/>
~Protect
</p>

<div><img src="/download/sprites/dp/242.png" alt="Blissey"/></div>
<p>
Blissey@Chople Berry<br/>
Calm<br/>
4 HP, 252 Def, 252 SpDef<br/>
~Icy Wind<br/>
~Toxic<br/>
~Softboiled<br/>
~Protect
</p>

<p>Yes, thats right, Blissey. I (and everybody else) realized the metagame was hugely special, and the majority of the few Physical Pokemon were used as Fake-Out leads, ie Hitmontop, Toxicroak, Infernape. Combine that with the fact that Metagross will be leading most likely, and will probably explode, Giratina often still looses to Blissey, and Groudon is easy to lure out with the temptation of altering the weather, and you have yourself a Blissey weak metagame. I found Kyogre Abamasnow to be a useful lead for Blissey, because they didn't really give Hitmontop, Toxicroak etc a reason to switch, while still beating them with Blizzard spam. Giratina was necessary as an anti Explosion measure, as a 2 for 1 Explosion turn one or two is a worst case scenario, forcing Blissey out without giving me the opportunity to weaken my opponents team where I wanted it weakened. I found Yache to be the more valuable Berry for Giratina with the rediculous amount of Blizzards running around, and the fact the Giratina is rarely 2HKO'd with Yache. That leaves the MVP, Blissey, Icy Wind allows Blissey to be a team Player, lowering things speeds so Giratina can avoid Spacial Rend and Shadow Force away, or Kyogre fire off a Blizzard before taking a Thunder. The rest is pretty self explanatory, fun for all.</p>
<p>I drove the last 3 hours of the trip from Dallas Saturday morning, and then arrived around noon. I went in and found Matt, who told me I should probably get in line soon as it was pretty long, so into line I went. Mingot came and found me to give me my Lugia, as I wasn't able to receive it over Wifi before I left because of a power outage. I stood in line with a nice Pokedad whose kids had done decently in the morning, and now he was trying his own hand, he however lost round 2.</p>

<h3>Game One</h3>
<p>This was actually one of my most difficult wins the day, but thats pretty much all I remember about it. I know it came down to a once Dragon Danced, once Icy Winded Feraligatr against Blissey and Giratina in the Rain, with Giratina having taken an Ice Punch already, but being up in the air. I Icy Winded with Blissey to drop Feraligatr's speed below Giratina's while Blissey ate a Waterfall for 80% and Feraligatr took a Shadow Force for about 75%, the next turn I outsped and Dragon Clawed ftw, gg.</p>

<h3>Game Two</h3>
<p>This guy was pretty cool, and said he was a Smogon lurker, I think I convinced him to come play in 
<a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=63545">Live Tournaments</a>
some time (shameless plug). He lead Ape+Palkia. I double Protected turn one to avoid Fake-Out and start 
Hail damage, then Double Blizzarded. Ape brought Abamasnow to Sash while Palkia Thundered Kyogre, the 
double Blizzard goes and brings both to red. I double protect for Hail damage so that Ice Shard can ko 
my choice of enemies next turn, but he double switches into Scizor and .... Blissey xD. I chuckle on the 
inside, but then quickly turn to the problem at hand. Scizor is a problem, it resists Ice, Dragon, and 
Ghost and is immune to Toxic, basically nothing but Kyogre can touch it. I protect with Obama, but he 
fires a HH'd Bullet Punch at Kyogre. However, Kyogre takes it with pride and fires off a Surf for 
significant damage to Scizor. This turn I Blizzard+Surf and he Bullet Punches Kyogre for the ko, Blizzard 
goes and ko's Scizor and freezes Blissey (more on frozen nurses later). In comes Ape for him, and Giratina 
for me. The rest of the match is uneventful as I Shadow Sneak away Palkia and Ape before they move again, 
while Blissey tries to defrost and Helping Hand. Finally I take down Blissey with Dragon Claw, gg.</p>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_02" alt=""/></div>
<p><em>My Round 2 opponent, mid battle.</em></p>

<h3>Game Three</h3>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_03" alt=""/></div>
<p><em>My Round 3 opponent, just before starting.</em></p>
<p>Well after two pretty intense opening matches I'm ready for something easy, and sure enough its a Milotic+Charizard lead. Though he manages to take out both Kyogre and Abamasnow with a double crit double Burn Heat Wave (Kyogre dies from burn damage way later in the match) I sweep through relatively easily, gg.</p>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_04" alt=""/></div>
<p><em>Me after getting through what would be my second haxxiest match of the day.</em></p>
<p>After finishing Round 3 round I went up to the the middle, and the next station to open up was on the screen, but I told the judge I'd really rather not (in order to not reveal Blissey too much) and that Dave had said I didn't have to, so he let me play somewhere else. Then the next two people to finish were a FlSt Pokemon league player, and Cakes who I totally called buddy rule on. The judge started jokingly giving me a hard time about being so demanding, asking me if I'd like it if he went and got me lunch too.</p>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_05" alt=""/></div>
<p><em>Talking to the judge.</em></p>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_06" alt=""/></div>
<p><em>Here. There. Where?</em></p>

<h3>Game Four</h3>
<p>This round I was starting to second guess Blissey against randoms and decide to bring Ludicolo instead, and so play Ludicolo+Kyogre / Abomasnow+Giratina. My opponent was a nice girl, her Psychic Snorlax, Ludicolo Ice Beaming, slower than Ludicolo, Rayquaza, and Stone Edging Mewtwo however were less nice, gg.</p>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_07" alt=""/></div>
<p><em>Round 4 from afar</em></p>
<div><img src="/media/vgc/2010_altanta_alaka_08" alt=""/></div>
